20573, Controller ID is Missing

Probable causes

Description
Controller ID is the controller's unique identity. It is by default
equal to the serial number of the controller's cabinet. The
software configuration of the controller is missing this identity
information.

The officially released main computer image has been replaced,
e.g., for the purpose of collecting diagnostic data for a specific
problem.
Recommended actions
If this is a production system, install an official RobotWare
release as soon as possible.

host key hash algorithm MD5 or SHA1. The used SFTP server

at remote host arg does not support any of them.

matches the one received.
